---
// Lesson 1 — one Anchor record resolving to a highlight in two different
// layouts. Geometry carried over verbatim from the original lesson HTML.
---
<svg viewBox="0 0 720 430" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img"
     aria-label="The same highlight shown in two different layouts, both resolving from one anchor record.">
  <defs>
    <marker id="ah" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" refX="7" refY="4.5" orient="auto">
      <path d="M0,0 L9,4.5 L0,9 z" fill="#9a7b27"/>
    </marker>
  </defs>

  <!-- Panel A : big serif -->
  <rect class="panel" x="20" y="20" width="310" height="120" rx="6"/>
  <text class="ptitle" x="34" y="42">LAYOUT A — large serif, vertical</text>
  <rect class="hl" x="87" y="58" width="76" height="20"/>
  <text class="verse" x="34" y="72">In the beginning was the</text>
  <text class="verse" x="34" y="98">Word, and the Word was</text>
  <text class="verse" x="34" y="124">with God&#8230;</text>

  <!-- Panel B : small, other translation -->
  <rect class="panel" x="390" y="20" width="310" height="120" rx="6"/>
  <text class="ptitle" x="404" y="42">LAYOUT B — small, other translation</text>
  <rect class="hl" x="447" y="59" width="58" height="16"/>
  <text class="verse" x="404" y="70" font-size="13">In the beginning was the Word,</text>
  <text class="verse" x="404" y="92" font-size="13">and the Word was with God&#8230;</text>

  <!-- arrows down to the record -->
  <path class="arrow" d="M150,150 C150,200 330,210 360,250"/>
  <path class="arrow" d="M560,150 C560,200 390,210 360,250"/>

  <!-- the anchor record -->
  <rect class="rec" x="150" y="255" width="420" height="92" rx="6"/>
  <text class="reclbl" x="170" y="280">STORED AS ONE ANCHOR (a scripture coordinate)</text>
  <text class="mono" x="170" y="306">{'{'} book: "John", chapter: 1, verse: 1, word_index: 2 {'}'}</text>
  <text class="bad"  x="170" y="330">✗ never stored as pixels {'{'} x: 340, y: 88, w: 120 {'}'}</text>

  <text class="cap" x="360" y="380" text-anchor="middle">Layout changes &#8594; the app re-finds the words at that coordinate &#8594; re-draws the mark.</text>
  <text class="cap" x="360" y="400" text-anchor="middle">One address, many renderings. That is the whole magic.</text>
</svg>

<style>
  .panel  { fill:#fff; stroke:#d8cdb8; stroke-width:1.5; }
  .ptitle { font:600 12px Georgia, serif; fill:#4a443d; }
  .verse  { font:16px Georgia, serif; fill:#1a1714; }
  .hl     { fill:#f6e29a; }
  .arrow  { stroke:#9a7b27; stroke-width:1.6; fill:none; marker-end:url(#ah); }
  .rec    { fill:#fbf3dc; stroke:#9a7b27; stroke-width:1.5; }
  .reclbl { font:600 12px Georgia, serif; fill:#9a7b27; }
  .mono   { font:13px "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace; fill:#1a1714; }
  .bad    { font:13px "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace; fill:#9a3b2f; }
  .cap    { font:italic 12px Georgia, serif; fill:#4a443d; }
</style>
